A) Quick sanity checks (run these first)
1) Confirm you’re in Bash Cloud Shell
echo "$SHELL"

You want /bin/bash.
If you see PowerShell/pwsh, switch Cloud Shell to Bash (top-left selector) or type bash to enter a bash session.

2) Confirm current subscription (this is the #1 cause)
az account show -o table
az account list -o table | head
3) Prove whether Central US resources exist in this subscription
az resource list --query "[?location=='centralus'] | length(@)" -o tsv

If that prints 0, then either:

resources are in a different subscription → run the script with -a (all subs), OR

your resources aren’t actually in centralus → list distinct locations:

az resource list --query "[?location!=null].location" -o tsv | sed '/^$/d' | sort -u

Also, verify the official location name:

az account list-locations --query "[?displayName=='Central US'].[name,displayName]" -o tabl
